stylometry: Safety stock is the extra inventory that is stored incase demand durring lead time is higher than expected. When setting the amount of safety stock you must consider the costs of not have stock versus the cost of holding one to it. When dealing with safety stock you must look at the z value and the dlt, giving you the neccisary amount of safety stock. You can also determine the reorder point by adding the safety stock to the expencted demand during lead time.
